The backview of the iPhone 11 pro max | Photo: MS POWER USER There are some three things that are certain in life – Death, bills and of course, the release of new iPhones. For the past few months, we have been anticipating the release of Apple’s new addition – the iPhone 11, Pro and Max. As expected, it has finally been released and of course, its new design has got Tech gurus and Apple fanatics talking and dropping reviews. The iPhone 11, as it’s presumably called, is expected to look and feel pretty familiar to anyone who’s touched or owned an iPhone X, iPhone XS, iPhone XS Max, or iPhone XR. With this in mind, it may be hard to be convinced to proceed on making a switch to this new addition since it may seem like there won’t be any much difference. But, in order to clear those doubts, here are reasons to buy the new addition: